		"title": "CVE-2020-6807 on Ubuntu 16.04 FIPS Certified (xenial) - medium",
		"description": "When a device was changed while a stream was about to be destroyed, the<code>stream-reinit</code> task may have been executed after the stream wasdestroyed, causing a use-after-free and a potentially exploitable crash.This vulnerability affects Thunderbird < 68.6, Firefox < 74, Firefox <ESR68.6, and Firefox ESR < 68.6.\n\n    Update Instructions:\n\n    Run `sudo pro fix CVE-2020-6807` to fix the vulnerability. The problem can be corrected\n    by updating your system to the following package versions:\n\nfirefox - 74.0+build3-0ubuntu0.16.04.1\nfirefox-geckodriver - 74.0+build3-0ubuntu0.16.04.1\nfirefox-mozsymbols - 74.0+build3-0ubuntu0.16.04.1\nNo subscription required\n\nthunderbird - 1:68.7.0+build1-0ubuntu0.16.04.2\nthunderbird-gnome-support - 1:68.7.0+build1-0ubuntu0.16.04.2\nthunderbird-mozsymbols - 1:68.7.0+build1-0ubuntu0.16.04.2\nxul-ext-calendar-timezones - 1:68.7.0+build1-0ubuntu0.16.04.2\nxul-ext-gdata-provider - 1:68.7.0+build1-0ubuntu0.16.04.2\nxul-ext-lightning - 1:68.7.0+build1-0ubuntu0.16.04.2\nNo subscription required",
